<% content_for :title, "About | hushpair" %>

<main class="shell legal-shell" id="main-content">
  <section class="card legal-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>About hushpair</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      hushpair is a private, text-only chat space for two people. No profiles, no feeds, no
      audience, and no pressure to turn a quiet conversation into a social product.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Why it exists</h2>
    <p>
      Most chat products are designed to expand: more identity, more permanence, more notifications,
      more sharing, more surface area. hushpair takes the opposite approach.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is built for small, deliberate conversations where low friction and privacy matter more than
      profiles, growth loops, or social features.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>What it is</h2>
    <ul class="legal-list">
      <li>A private room for two people.</li>
      <li>Joinable by invite link.</li>
      <li>Text only.</li>
      <li>Anonymous by default.</li>
      <li>Temporary by design.</li>
      <li>Built with a strong preference for data minimization.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>What it is not</h2>
    <ul class="legal-list">
      <li>Not a social network.</li>
      <li>Not a group chat platform.</li>
      <li>Not a place for advertising, audience building, or identity graphs.</li>
      <li>Not designed to keep more data than it needs.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Product principles</h2>
    <ul class="legal-list">
      <li>Keep setup friction low.</li>
      <li>Keep rooms small and temporary.</li>
      <li>Keep data collection minimal.</li>
      <li>Keep the interface quiet and compact.</li>
      <li>Keep abuse prevention in scope from day one.</li>
      <li>Keep the product honest about its limits.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>Privacy posture</h2>
    <p>
      hushpair aims to avoid collecting identity data it does not need. Chat messages and nicknames
      are protected at rest, sensitive request parameters are filtered from logs, and rooms are designed
      to expire automatically rather than accumulate indefinitely.
    </p>
    <p>
      Privacy here is a product decision, not just a policy statement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card legal-card">
    <h2>What to expect</h2>
    <p>
      hushpair is intentionally narrow. It is built for simple invite-link conversations, not for
      social discovery, broad moderation workflows, or long-term message archives.
    </p>
    <p>
      hushpair is experimental software. Please do not use it for sensitive, emergency, regulated,
      or legally important communications.
    </p>
  </section>
</main>
